					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>435 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>330</height>
										<width>245</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>205</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>435 folios (+ 3 unfoliated modern paper flyleaves and 1 unfoliated and 1 foliated older paper flyleaves at the beginning, and 1 unfoliated older flyleaf and 3 unfoliated modern paper flyleaves). </p>
									<p>Hebrew foliation is the continuation of that of the first volume (folio 2 is identical with Hebrew foliation 293). Unfoliated leaf [folio 160*] after folio 160 (but it has the Hebrew foliation: 452) and one unfoliated leaf [folio 436] after folio 435.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>53 quires: i8 (folios 2-9), ii8 (folios 10-17), iii8 (folios 18-25), iv8 (folios 26-33), v8 (folios 34-41), vi8 (folios 42-49), vii8 (folios 50-57), viii8 (folios 58-65), ix8 (folios 66-73), x8 (folios 74-81), xi10 (folios 82-93), xii8 (folios 94-101), xiii8 (folios 102-109), xiv8 (folios110-117), xv8 (folios 118-125), xvi8 (folios 126-133), xvii8 (folios 134-141), xviii8 (folios 142-149), xix12 (folios 150-[161*]), xx8 (folios 161-168), xxi8 (folios 169-176), xxii6 (folios 177-182), xxiii6 (folios 183-188), xxiv8 (folios 189-196), xxv8 (folios 197-204), xxvi8 (folios 205-212), xxvii8 (folios 213-220), xxviii8 (folios 221-228), xxix8 (folios 229-236), xxx8 (folios 237-244), xxxi8 (folios 245-252), xxxii8 (folios 253-260), xxxiii8 (folios 261-268), xxxiv8 (folios 269-276), xxxv8 (folios 277-284), xxxvi8 (folios 285-292), xxxvii10 (folios 293-302), xxxviii10 (folios 303-312), xxxix8 (folios 313-320), xl8 (folios 321-328), xli8 (folios 329-336), xlii8 (folios 337-344), xliii10 (folios 345-354), xliv8 (folios 355-362), xlv8 (folios 363-370), xlvi8 (folios 371-378), xlvii8 (folios 379-386), xlviii10 (folios 387-396), xlix8 (folios 397-404), l8 (folios 405-412), li8 (folios 413-420), lii8 (folios 421-428), liii8 (folios 429-[436]).</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="36" writtenLines="36">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible ruling with a sharp object (complete). Hair-side and flesh-side are distinguishable.
</p>
									<p>Scant marginal notes. </p>
									<p>Fore edge, lower and upper edges are colored with red strips.
</p>
									<p>Manicula in the margin (folio 17r).</p>
									<p>The spaces for diagrams in Sefer ῾avodah have been left blank.</p>
									<p>The unfoliated older paper flyleaves have watermarks similar to <ref target="Heawood_1950" type="number">447, 2745</ref>, the foliated paper flyleaf has a watermark similar to <ref target="Heawood_1950" type="number">750</ref>.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi square script, unpunctuated, of the 15th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Shelomoh ibn Alzuḳ</name> : inscribed in the colophon, folio 434v.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Written by Shelomoh ben Alzuḳ for <name type="person" role="patron">Yosef ben Daṿid ben Shelomoh ben Rabi Daṿid ben Gedalyah the elder</name>: inscription (folio 434v).
</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Laurentius Franguellus</name>: inscribed with his name: 'Revistu[s] p[er] me Laurentiu[s] Franguellu[s] die 26 novembris 1574' (folio 434r), see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="number">105-110</ref>.
</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Luigi de Bologna</name>: inscribed 'Revisto et corretto per me f. Luigi da Bologna del 1601' (folio 433v). A converted Jew working for the Inquisition as censor (active at the end of the sixteenth, beginning of seventeenth century), see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">104</ref>, and appendix § 112-117.
</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Camillo Jaghel</name>: inscribed with his name, <date calendar="Gregorian">1613 </date>(folio 433v), see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="number">50-56</ref>.
</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Renato de Modena</name>: inscription 'Visto p[er] me fr. Renato de Mod[ena] 1626' (f. 434); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="number">132-133</ref>.
</p>
							<p>Erasures (e.g. <locus n="224v, 283r, 294v, 297r, 375r, 422r"/>).
</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Bernard Mould </name>(b. c. 1683; d. 1744), chaplain at Smyrna: inscribed with his name, <name type="place">Smyrna</name>, <date calendar="Gregorian">1724 </date>(folio 435b); sold to <name type="person" role="owner">Edward Harley</name> on 28 July 1725 (see <ref target="Wright_1966"/>, <ref target="Wright_1972"/>).</p>
						</additions>
